Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. In a large bowl, whisk together the Teriyaki marinade, lemon juice, ginger and lemon pepper. Add the shredded cabbage, mushrooms, pea pods, scallions, and red pepper. Toss to coat everything. Lightly oil a baking pan, place the tilapia in the pan. Pour the vegetables and sauce over the fish and tightly cover the pan with foil. Bake at 375 degrees F for 20 minutes.